# =============================================================================
# Developer-only: OAuth credentials for calendar sign-in
# =============================================================================
# End users never see or enter these values — set them once here, then rebuild.
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the client IDs below.
#
# See README.md → "Calendar OAuth (developer setup)" for Azure / Google steps.

# Microsoft Outlook / Microsoft 365 (required for Microsoft calendar connect)
# Register ONE app at https://entra.microsoft.com → App registrations → New registration:
#   - Name: Candor
#   - Account types: "Accounts in any org directory and personal Microsoft accounts"
#   - Redirect URI: Mobile and desktop → http://localhost:8765/callback
#   - Authentication → Allow public client flows: Yes
#   - API permissions (Microsoft Graph delegated): User.Read, Calendars.ReadWrite, offline_access
#
# One line is enough — picked up by Vite (frontend) and Rust (via src-tauri/build.rs):
VITE_MS_CLIENT_ID=your-azure-application-client-id-here

# Google Calendar (required for Google calendar connect)
# Register ONE OAuth client at https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials:
#   - Enable Google Calendar API
#   - Create OAuth client → Desktop app (no secret) OR Web application (needs secret below)
#   - Redirect URI: http://localhost:8721/oauth/google/callback
#   - Scope: https://www.googleapis.com/auth/calendar.readwrite
#
# One line is enough for the client ID (same Vite + Rust wiring as Microsoft):
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-oauth-client-id-here

# Google client secret (Web application OAuth clients only; not needed for Desktop app type)
# CANDOR_GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-google-client-secret-here

# After editing .env, restart the app so both frontend and Rust pick up changes:
#   npm run tauri:dev
